/* This file must contain the required information of the model parameters including:

- P_init: Value for initialize the parameters. Alternatively, the user can provide a file with a list of X volumes (different lines) to initialize the P parameters at each voxel (one file name for each parameter) and same dimensions than input data: argument --init_params='file_list' at the command line. If a line L is empty in the list, the initialization of that parameter is set to P_init[L]. If not any method is used, parameters are initialized to 0.

- Priors: you can set a prior for each parameter: prior[p]=Type()
Type can be: Bounded(min,max), Gaussian(mean,sd), Gamma(alpha,beta), sin(), ARD()
If not specified any, non-informative priors are used

- CFP: Common Fixed paramaters to all the voxels. Size is T x Measurements. For example, bvals is 1XM, bvecs is 3xM. The user will need to use an input file with the list of the name of the files that contain their values. To specify the file with the list, the user will use the argument --CFP='file_list' at the command line.
You must specify T size  each parameter -> CFP_size

Use this format:
NPARAMS=X
P_init[V1,V2,V3,...]
prior[0]=Bounded(min,max)
prior[1]=sin()
...
CFP_size[T1,T2,..]

The starting mark for the specification of the model parameters is NEWMODEL
The number of parameters specified here must be the same as in the functions file and must follow the same order
*/

// In DTI model the parameters are:
// [S0,Dxx,Dxy,Dxz,Dyy,Dyz,Dzz]

NEW_MODEL

// Alternatively, the user can use the argument --init_params='file_list' at the command line.
// If not specified, initialized to 0
//P_init[4000,0.006,0.000000001,0.000000001,0.006,0.000000001,0.006]
P_init[2000,0,0,0,0,0,0]

// Priors. It can be one of these:
// Bounded(min,max), Gaussian(mean,sd), Gamma(alpha,beta), sin(), ARD()
// If not specified any, non-informative priors are used
prior[0]=Bounded(300,3500)

// bvecs,bvals
CFP_size[3,1]


